cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about distributed computing systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with the completion time of a system with independent exponentially distributed machine service times.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the effect of redundancy on the latency in a distributed system.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with the assignment of tasks to machines in a distributed system.
- cs.PF (Performance) is also relevant as the paper studies the expected completion time of distributed computing algorithms.
